defs.name: is_nan
defs.docs: Returns `true` if this value is `NaN` and `false` otherwise.

defs.name: is_infinite
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if this value is positive infinity or negative infinity and `false`
 otherwise.

defs.name: is_finite
defs.docs: Returns `true` if this number is neither infinite nor `NaN`.

defs.name: is_normal
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the number is neither zero, infinite, subnormal, or `NaN`.

defs.docs: Returns the floating point category of the number.

defs.docs: Returns a number that represents the sign of `self`.

defs.name: is_sign_positive
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if and only if `self` has a positive sign, including `+0.0`, `NaNs` with
 positive sign bit and positive infinity.

defs.name: is_sign_negative
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if and only if `self` has a negative sign, including `-0.0`, `NaNs` with
 negative sign bit and negative infinity.
